{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "Translation table: Rocksmith gear knob → VST parameter. Curated around Kilohearts Essentials (free) — consistent param names across the entire bundle.",
    "version": 3,
    "updated": "2026-05-28",
    "schema": {
      "<rs_gear_type>": {
        "<vst_name_stem_lowercased>": {
          "<rs_knob_name>": {
            "param": "<exact VST param name as shown in the in-app editor>",
            "scale": "<float, multiply RS value by this. 0.01 for 0-100 → 0-1; 0.0005 for ms 0-2000; 1.0 for direct dB / semitones>",
            "offset": "<optional float, added after scale>",
            "invert": "<optional bool, replaces v with (1-v) after scale>"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "kilohearts_param_naming_convention": {
      "_note": "KHS modules use consistent param names across the entire Essentials bundle. Common params you'll see in every module:",
      "rate":     "Rate (Hz, 0-1 internal)",
      "depth":    "Depth (0-1)",
      "feedback": "Feedback (0-1)",
      "mix":      "Dry/Wet (0-1) — some older docs show 'Mix'; the in-app editor will show the real name",
      "cutoff":   "Cutoff (0-1, log freq)",
      "drive":    "Drive (0-1)",
      "threshold":"Threshold (dB)",
      "ratio":    "Ratio (1:N)",
      "time":     "Time (s or 0-1 normalised)",
      "pitch":    "Pitch (semitones)"
    },
    "notes": [
      "If a param name doesn't match, open the in-app VST editor for that gear, copy the exact label from a slider, and paste here. The lookup is case-insensitive but otherwise exact.",
      "VST name stems below are lowercased to match the case-insensitive lookup. Plugin files on disk are 'kHs Chorus.vst3' etc. — the matcher strips '.vst3' and lowercases automatically.",
      "EQ pedals (EQ5/EQ8/BassEQ8): knobs are absolute frequencies (e.g. '5700': 5 = +5 dB at 5700 Hz). kHs 3-Band EQ can absorb three of those — the entries below pick the most musical bands. The other RS frequencies are silently dropped."
    ]
  },

